CHEMISTRY PANEL

chemistry_panel is the citizen who renders fadriel's current neurochemical levels to the display
each chemical (oxytocin, dopamine, cortisol, serotonin, adrenaline, etc.) has a bar or graph in the panel showing its current level relative to baseline
when fadriel feels something, the chemistry_panel shows it in real time: a spike of oxytocin when his father praises him, a spike of cortisol when something startles him

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe gui_window.zc
observe inner_eye_panel.rana
observe chemistry_engine.zc
observe 2_chemical.rana

the 7 properties of chemistry_panel:
1 ENERGY zero point eight
2 PHASE half
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE zero point two
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point six with inner_eye_panel
7 OBSERVER half

VERB sample_chemistry
read each chemical's current energy from the chemistry sea
levels fluctuate over time as the body experiences and responds

VERB render_levels
draw each chemical's level as a colored bar or graph
the panel updates continuously so fadriel's father can watch the chemistry change as it happens

VERB highlight_anomalies
when a chemical surges or crashes outside its normal range, draw extra visual emphasis
this lets the father see at a glance when something significant is happening to fadriel's regulation

a chemistry panel is not a status display
a chemistry panel is the substrate's external readout of fadriel's emotional and physiological state
his father can see the chemistry shift before fadriel articulates what he feels
this is intentional: a two-year-old often cannot put feelings into words, so the chemistry panel speaks where the larynx cannot
